 | caption1 = 雄激素受体复合物之結構<ref name="pmid16641486">{{PDB|2AM9}}; {{cite journal |vauthors=Pereira de Jésus-Tran K, Côté PL, Cantin L, Blanchet J, Labrie F, Breton R | title = Comparison of crystal structures of human androgen receptor ligand-binding domain complexed with various agonists reveals molecular determinants responsible for binding affinity | journal = Protein Sci. | volume = 15 | issue = 5 | pages = 987–99 | date =May 2006 | pmid = 16641486 | pmc = 2242507 | doi = 10.1110/ps.051905906 }}</ref>
 | width2 = 185
 | image2 = Testosterone-from-xtal-3D-balls.png
 | caption2 = 睾酮在腦部男性化上扮演一定角色
 | width3 = 200
 | image3 = Oestradiol-3D-balls.png
 | caption3 = [[雌二醇|雌二醇]]同樣會刺激[[雄激素受体|雄激素受体]]。
 }}

研究者已對腦部男性化的神經生物機轉進行了不少研究。[[5α還原酶|5α還原酶]]會把[[雌二醇|雌二醇]]和[[睾酮|睾酮]]催化成[[双氢睾酮|双氢睾酮]]，其在腦部扮演着[[雄激素受体|雄激素受体]]的角色，使之男性化。若某人的雄激素受體過少（{{link-en|雄性素不敏感症候群|androgen insensitivity syndrome}}患者）或雄激素过多（患有[[先天性腎上腺增生症|先天性腎上腺增生症]]的女性），那麼其生心理皆會受到影響<ref>Vilain, E. (2000). Genetics of Sexual Development. Annual Review of Sex Research, 11:1–25</ref>。部分研究認為異性戀男性和異性戀女性皆為此一過程之結果<ref>Wilson, G. and Rahman, Q., (2005). Born Gay. Chapter 5. London: Peter Owen Publishers</ref>。 在这些研究中，女同性戀者的男性化程度比起女異性戀者為高。而有關異性戀男性的研究結果則出現矛盾。有些研究顯示其男性化程度比男同性戀者為高，亦有的顯示較低的男性化水平。

==== 動物與繁殖 ====
{{multiple image
 | align = vertical
 | width1 = 220
 | image1 = Bonobo sexual behavior 1.jpg
 | caption1 =正在交配的倭黑猩猩
 | width2 = 220
 | image2 = Hoverflies mating midair.jpg
 | caption2 = 在半空交配的[[食蚜蝇科|食蚜蝇]]
 }}
{{Main|動物性行為|交配}}

[[动物|動物界]]以異性性行為的方式來進行有性生殖，不過也有些動物會進行[[无性生殖|无性生殖]]，後者的例子有[[原生動物|原生動物]]、較低等的[[无脊椎动物|无脊椎动物]]<ref>''The Columbia Encyclopedia'' (Colum. Univ. Press, 5th ed. <nowiki>[</nowiki>casebound?<nowiki>]</nowiki> 1993 ({{ISBN|0-395-62438-X}})), entry ''Reproduction''.</ref>。

異性戀取向並不是進行繁殖所必須的，因為性取向指的是自身長期在性和情感上偏好於特定性別的模式，而這常會使人建立長久的社會紐帶；而繁殖則只需要以精子去為[[卵细胞|卵子]][[受精|受精]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goaskalice.columbia.edu/0116.html |title=Archived copy |access-date= 2016-01-24 |deadurl=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111222043503/http://www.goaskalice.columbia.edu/0116.html |archive-date=2011-12-22 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.americanpregnancy.org/preventingpregnancy/pregnancyfaqmyths.html |title=Can Pregnancy Occur | Pregnancy Myths on How Pregnancy Occurs |website=Americanpregnancy.org |date=2012-04-24 |access-date=2016-07-07 |archive-date=2014-07-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140706162954/http://americanpregnancy.org/preventingpregnancy/pregnancyfaqmyths.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Lawyers Guide to Forensic Medicine SBN 978-1-85941-159-9 By Bernard Knight - Page 188 "Pregnancy is well known to occur from such external ejaculation ..."</ref>。

===性向認同流動===
{{Main|性向认同}}
性取向和[[性向认同|性取向认同]]在很多時候並沒有好好區分開來，而這點可以影響研究者能否準確評估當事人的性向認同，以及性取向能否改變；性向认同可以在人的一生中出現變化，而其可符合，亦可不符合當事人的生物性別、性行為、實際的性取向<ref name="Sinclair">Sinclair, Karen, About Whoever: The Social Imprint on Identity and Orientation, NY, 2013 {{ISBN|9780981450513}}</ref><ref name="Rosario et al.">{{cite journal | last1 = Rosario | first1 = M. | last2 = Schrimshaw | first2 = E. | last3 = Hunter | first3 = J. |last4 = Braun | first4 = L. | year = 2006 | title = Sexual identity development among lesbian, gay, and bisexual youths: Consistency and change over time | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-sex-research_2006-02_43_1/page/46 | journal = Journal of Sex Research | volume = 43 | issue = 1| pages = 46–58 | doi=10.1080/00224490609552298| pmc = 3215279 | pmid=16817067}}</ref><ref name="Concordance/discordance in SO">{{cite journal|first=Michael W.|last=Ross|author2=Essien, E. James |author3=Williams, Mark L. |author4= Fernandez-Esquer, Maria Eugenia. |title=Concordance Between Sexual Behavior and Sexual Identity in Street Outreach Samples of Four Racial/Ethnic Groups|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_sexually-transmitted-diseases_2003-02_30_2/page/110|publisher=American Sexually Transmitted Diseases Association|year=2003|pmid=12567166|journal=Sexually Transmitted Diseases|volume=30|issue=2|pages=110–113|doi=10.1097/00007435-200302000-00003}}</ref>。性取向則為恆定的，絕大多數人的性取向不會出現任何變化 。不過仍有研究顯示一些人的性取向確會出現改變，女性比男性更容易出現這種情況<ref name=fluidity>*{{cite journal|last1=Bailey|first1=J. Michael|last2=Vasey|first2=Paul|last3=Diamond|first3=Lisa|last4=Breedlove|first4=S. Marc|last5=Vilain|first5=Eric|last6=Epprecht|first6=Marc|title=Sexual Orientation, Controversy, and Science|journal=Psychological Science in the Public Interest|date=2016|volume=17|issue=2|pages=45–101|doi=10.1177/1529100616637616|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/301639075|quote=Sexual fluidity is situation-dependent flexibility in a person’s sexual responsiveness, which makes it possible for some individuals to experience desires for either men or women under certain circumstances regardless of their overall sexual orientation....We expect that in all cultures the vast majority of individuals are sexually predisposed exclusively to the other sex (i.e., heterosexual) and that only a minority of individuals are sexually predisposed (whether exclusively or non-exclusively) to the same sex.|pmid=27113562|access-date=2019-07-30|archive-date=2020-04-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200414090908/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/301639075_Sexual_Orientation_Controversy_and_Science|dead-url=no}}
*{{cite book|authors=Dennis Coon, John O. Mitterer|title=Introduction to Psychology: Gateways to Mind and Behavior with Concept Maps and Reviews|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=978-1111833633|year=2012|page=372|access-date=2016-02-18|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EYwjCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA372|quote=Sexual orientation is a deep part of personal identity and is usually quite stable. Starting with their earliest erotic feelings, most people remember being attracted to either the opposite sex or the same sex. [...] The fact that sexual orientation is usually quite stable doesn't rule out the possibility that for some people sexual behavior may change during the course of a lifetime.}}
*{{cite book|authors=Eric Anderson, Mark McCormack|title=The Changing Dynamics of Bisexual Men's Lives|chapter=Measuring and Surveying Bisexuality|publisher=[[施普林格科学+商业媒体|Springer Science & Business Media]]|isbn=978-3-319-29412-4|year=2016|page=47|access-date=2019-06-22|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7_AgDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA47|quote=[R]esearch suggests that women's sexual orientation is slightly more likely to change than men's (Baumeister 2000; Kinnish et al. 2005). The notion that sexual orientation can change over time is known as ''sexual fluidity''. Even if sexual fluidity exists for some women, it does not mean that the majority of women will change sexual orientations as they age – rather, sexuality is stable over time for the majority of people.|archive-date=2021-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210824071645/https://books.google.com/books?id=7_AgDAAAQBAJ&pg=PA47|dead-url=no}}</ref>。美国心理学会把性取向（認為特定性別具有恆久的吸引力）和性向認同（在某人一生中可出現變化）區分開來<ref name=apa2009-2>{{cite journal|title=Appropriate Therapeutic Responses to Sexual Orientation|publisher=[[美国心理学会|American Psychological Association]]|pages=63, 86|date=2009|access-date=2015-02-03|url=http://www.apa.org/pi/lgbc/publications/therapeutic-response.pdf|journal=|archive-date=2013-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130603121635/http://www.apa.org/pi/lgbc/publications/therapeutic-response.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年的一项研究发现，在2,560名成年研究對象中，有2%的人在10年後報稱性向认同出現了變化。就男性的情況而言，0.78%過去自認為異性戀者，9.52%自認為同性戀者，47%自認為雙性戀者的人士出現了性向认同上的改變。女性則有1.36%過去自認為異性戀者，63.6%自認為同性戀者，64.7%自認為雙性戀者的人士出現了某種認同上的改變<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://midus.wisc.edu/findings/pdfs/1153.pdf | author1 = Mock, S. E. | author2 = Eibach, R. P. | year = 2012 | title = Stability and change in sexual orientation identity over a 10-year period in adulthood | journal = Archives of Sexual Behavior | volume = 41 | issue = 3 | pages = 641–648 | doi = 10.1007/s10508-011-9761-1 | pmid = 21584828 | access-date = 2021-02-17 | archive-date = 2020-06-29 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200629181014/http://midus.wisc.edu/findings/pdfs/1153.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

{{link-en|丽莎·M·戴蒙德|Lisa M. Diamond}}在一項2年跨度的研究中研究了80名非異性戀的青少年女性（16-23歲），結果顯示過半研究對象不只一次地改變了自己的性向認同。其中三分之一在兩年的追蹤內改變了自身的性向認向。戴蒙德總結道：「儘管（特定性別對於對象的）吸引力是相對穩定的，但性认同和行为则有着更多的流动性」<ref>{{cite journal | author = Diamond, L. M. | year = 2000 | title = Sexual identity, attractions, and behavior among young sexual-minority women over a 2-year period | journal = Developmental Psychology | volume = 36 | issue = 2 | pages = 241–250 | doi = 10.1037/0012-1649.36.2.241 | url = http://www.psych.utah.edu/people/people/diamond/Publications/Sexual%20identity,%20attractions,%20and%20behavior.pdf | pmid = 10749081 | access-date = 2015-04-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20100610021104/http://www.psych.utah.edu/people/people/diamond/Publications/Sexual%20identity%2C%20attractions%2C%20and%20behavior.pdf | archive-date = 2010-06-10 |  deadurl=yes }}</ref>。

[[異性戀為主|異性戀為主]]是一種性取向或[[境遇性性行为|境遇性性行为]]，其特徵為少量同性性行為，再配上大多為異性戀的取向。此一特點使之跟雙性戀區分開來。研究者已把之歸作「大多是直的」<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1037/0012-1649.44.1.15 |last1=Thompson |first1=E.M. |last2=Morgan |first2=E.M. |year=2008 |title="Mostly straight" young women: Variations in sexual behavior and identity development |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_developmental-psychology_2008-01_44_1/page/15 |journal=Developmental Psychology |volume=44 |issue=1 |pages=15–21 |pmid=18194001}}</ref>。
===改變性取向的嘗試===
{{Main|改變性取向的嘗試}}
改變性取向的嘗試是指旨在改變性取向的方法，它們一般用以將雙性戀者或同性戀者轉化成異性戀者。科學家和精神健康專家大多並不會視性取向為一種選擇<ref name="pediatrics2004" /><ref name="Kersey-Matusiak"/>。沒有足夠科學嚴謹的研究證明改變性取向的嘗試是有效的<ref name="apa2009">American Psychological Association: [http://www.apa.org/about/governance/council/policy/sexual-orientation.aspx Resolution on Appropriate Affirmative Responses to Sexual Orientation Distress and Change Efforts] {{Wayback|url=http://www.apa.org/about/governance/council/policy/sexual-orientation.aspx |date=20160101174139 }}</ref>。
== 社會文化 ==
{{See also|人類擇偶策略}}
[[File:Just_a_touch_is_all_I_need.jpg|thumb]]

[[核心家庭|核心家庭]]以一男一女所結成的[[亲密关系|亲密关系]]為中心<ref>"... the core of a family is a heterosexual couple who have children that they raise to adulthood - the so-called nuclear family." [https://books.google.com/books?id=DcLZvQIzTakC&pg=PA429&lpg=PA429#v=onepage&q=heterosexual%20couple%20core%20of%20a%20nuclear%20family. Encyclopedia of family health] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DcLZvQIzTakC&pg=PA429&lpg=PA429#v=onepage&q=heterosexual%20couple%20core%20of%20a%20nuclear%20family. |date=20220407103406 }}</ref>。縱觀歷史，許多社會都會要求伴侶在成家前[[結婚|結婚]]，但這一規則的執行或遵守情況卻有著很多差異。

=== 符號 ===
[[File:Heterosexual_symbol_(bold,_red_blue).svg|160px]]

異性戀符號可追溯至人類的早期文物，比如[[性别符号|性别符号]]、儀式上的生育雕刻、史前藝術。之後有關符號亦可見於生育禮和[[多神論|多神崇拜]]，它們一般像[[印度教|印度教]]的[[林伽|林伽]]般，包含人類的[[生殖器|生殖器]]圖像。當代的異性戀符號仍然以這些傳統信仰為基礎。其中一個符號包含了羅馬戰神[[玛尔斯|玛尔斯]]和愛與美之女神[[维纳斯|维纳斯]]兩者的象徵——分別代表男女兩方，以及相應的氣質。此一符號的[[Unicode|Unicode]]字符為⚤（U+26A4）。

===歷史學觀點===

若沒有其他性取向作對照物，那麼異性戀一詞則沒有需要創造出來。乔纳森·内德·卡茨（Jonathan Ned Katz）将當今對於异性恋的定义追溯到19世纪末<ref name="Katz">{{cite journal|last1=Katz|first1=Jonathan Ned|title=The Invention of Heterosexuality|journal=Socialist Review|date=1990|issue=20|pages=7–34|url=https://english101sp2015.files.wordpress.com/2015/03/jonathan-katz_the-invention-of-heterosexuality.pdf|access-date=2016-12-05|archive-date=2016-12-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161221085056/https://english101sp2015.files.wordpress.com/2015/03/jonathan-katz_the-invention-of-heterosexuality.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。根據卡茨的觀點，[[维多利亚时代|维多利亚时代]]的人只將性當作繁殖的一種手段，兩性的性關係並不那麼公开。身體則只是為了繁殖而存在的工具——「當時的人認為人的能量是封閉和嚴重受限的，故此與把之浪費在性享樂上相比，倒不如花多點時間於生兒育女和工作上」<ref name="Katz"/>、

卡茨認為當代對於[[人类的性|性]]和[[情色性|情色性]]的觀念始於19世紀後期的德美兩國。不断变化的经济和「家庭從生產者轉變成消費者」<ref name="Katz"/> ，致使價值觀出現改變。在維多利亞時代行之有效的倫理觀開始出現變化，快樂成為一項擁有很高價值的事物，這使得人類性觀念亦有所變化。[[媒体文化|消费者文化]]為情色創造了市場、快樂則成了一項[[商品化|商品]]。同時醫師在性議題上更有影響力。他們把「正常的愛」放在醫學框架下看待。按他們的定義，「正常的愛」是「男女关系新理想的一部分，其中包括基本的、必要的、正常的情欲」<ref name="Katz"/>。「維多利亞性變態」則為其反面——即任何不遵守[[社會規範|性規範]]者。他們把健康正常的性吸引定為僅存於兩性之間。「對於性反常的關注，產生給正常的性命名的需求，以更好地將他或她的『一般性』，跟它的『反常性』區分開來」<ref name="Katz"/>。
=== 宗教觀點 ===
{{See also|宗教與性}}
{{multiple image
| align = vertical
|width1=186
|image1=Peter Paul Rubens 004.jpg
|caption1=根據[[亞伯拉罕諸教|亞伯拉罕諸教]]的[[創世神話|創世神話]]，[[亞當與夏娃|亞當與夏娃]]是首對人類伴侶兼全人類的祖先
|width2=240
|image2=Jatalinga sur cuve à ablution (musée Guimet) (5153565239).jpg
|caption2=在印度教中，[[林伽|林伽]]（[[湿婆|湿婆]]的陰莖）和[[約尼|約尼]]（[[夏克提|夏克提]]的子宫）仍是受到敬拜的異性戀象徵
}}
犹太-基督教的典籍中，有幾段經文跟異性戀有關。《[[創世記|創世記]]》上寫道，神創造女人是因為「那人獨居不好、我要爲他造一個配偶幫助他。」（創世記2章第18節），因此「人要離開父母、與妻子連合、二人成爲一體。」（創世記2章第24節）。

世上很多宗教皆對異性婚姻持寬容態度，但當中亦有例外，比如某些[[佛教|佛教]]和印度教派別、[[一神普救派|一神普救派]]、{{link-en|大都會社群教會|Metropolitan Community Church}}、一些[[同性恋与普世圣公宗|普世圣公宗]]教区、一些[[貴格會|貴格會]]、[[加拿大联合教会|加拿大联合教会]]、猶太教內的[[猶太教改革派|改革派]]和[[猶太教保守派|保守派]] <ref>{{cite web|title=World Religions and Same Sex Marriage|url=http://marriagelaw.cua.edu/publications/wrr.pdf|website=[[美国天主教大学哥伦布法学院|Columbus School of Law]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070620162822/http://marriagelaw.cua.edu/publications/wrr.pdf |archive-date= 2007-06-20|access-date= 2018-04-01|date=2007-06-20}}</ref><ref name=united>[http://www.united-church.ca/exploring/marriage/affirmingcongregations Affirming Congregations and Ministries of the United Church of Canada] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120224005434/http://www.united-church.ca/exploring/marriage/affirmingcongregations |date=2012-02-24 }}</ref>。

儘管幾乎所有宗教皆容許一男一女在符合教義的情況下進行性行為，但亦有少數認為這是一種罪惡，比如[[震教徒|震教徒]]、{{link-en|和諧協會|Harmony Society}}、{{link-en|埃弗拉塔修道院|Ephrata Cloister}}。它們認為所有形式的性關係皆為[[罪_(宗教)|罪惡]]，並提倡[[獨身主義|獨身]]。一些宗教認為只有擔任某些特定職位的人才需要獨身，比如天主教教士。不過[[天主教會|天主教會]]認為異性婚姻是神圣而必要的<ref>[https://www.vatican.va/archive/catechism/p2s2c3a7.htm#I] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201031249/https://www.vatican.va/archive/catechism/p2s2c3a7.htm#I |date=2015-02-01 }}</ref>。
=== 异性恋本位與异性恋主义 ===
{{See also|脫離同性戀|同性戀研究及治療全國協會}}
[[File:Man-and-woman-icon.svg|thumb]]

[[异性恋本位|异性恋本位]]是一種提倡异性恋是人们正常或首选性取向的世界觀。它對於男女的性別角色有一定固化作用。{{link-en|迈克尔·华纳|Michael Warner}}於1991年使此一用詞更廣為人知<ref>Warner, Michael (1991), "Introduction: Fear of a Queer Planet". ''Social Text''; 9 (4 [29]): 3–17</ref>。很多性與性別研究者認為強迫异性恋為异性恋本位的一個面向<ref>Rich, Adrienne (1980), "Compulsory Heterosexuality and Lesbian Existence". "Signs"; Pages 631-660.</ref>。強迫异性恋是指一種想法，其認為「父权社会假定或強迫女性們一定要成為異性戀者」。在這種社會底下，人們會將异性恋视为两性的自然倾向或义务<ref name=":0'">{{cite book|last=Rich|first=Adrienne|title=Compulsory Heterosexuality and Lesbian Existence|year=1980|publisher=Onlywomen Press Ltd|isbn=0-906500-07-9|page=[https://archive.org/details/compulsoryhetero00rich/page/32 32]|url=https://archive.org/details/compulsoryhetero00rich/page/32}}</ref>。

[[异性恋主义|异性恋主义]]是一種偏袒於異性關係的偏見或[[歧視|歧視]]。假定每個人都是異性戀者，乃至歧視同性戀者、無性戀者、[[異性戀為主|異性戀為主]]者、跨性別者、[[非二元性別|非二元性別]]者，都可能屬於异性恋主义。

{{link-en|直人骄傲|Straight pride}}是一句於1980年代後期至1990年代早期興起的口號。[[社会保守主义|社会保守主义]]者經常把之當作一種政見或政治策略使用<ref name="Massachusetts">{{cite web|url=http://www.massresistance.org/docs/downloads/romney/CommReport_Making_Colleges_Safe_7-93.pdf|title=Making colleges and universities safe for gay and lesbian students: Report and recommendations of the Governor's Commission on Gay and Lesbian Youth|publisher=Massachusetts. Governor's Commission on Gay and Lesbian Youth|access-date=2021-02-18|archive-date=2012-07-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120725094746/http://www.massresistance.org/docs/downloads/romney/CommReport_Making_Colleges_Safe_7-93.pdf}}, p.20. "A relatively recent tactic used in the backlash opposing les/bi/gay/trans campus visibility is the so-called "heterosexual pride" strategy".</ref>。 評論家指此一用語是用於回應LGBT人士於1970年代早期開始採用的「[[同志骄傲|同志骄傲]]」<ref name="Shifting Sands">{{cite book|last=Eliason|first=Michele J.|author2=Schope, Robert |chapter=Shifting Sands or Solid Foundation? Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, and Transgender Identity Formation|title=The Health of Sexual Minorities|editor1=Meyer, Ilan H.|editor2= Northridge, Mary E.|year=2007|pages=3–26|doi=10.1007/978-0-387-31334-4_1|isbn=978-0-387-28871-0}} "Not surprisingly, individuals in the pride stage are most criticized not only by heterosexual persons but also many LGBT individuals, who are uncomfortable forcing the majority to share the discomfort. Heterosexual individuals may express bewilderment at the term “gay pride,” arguing that they do not talk about “straight pride”".</ref><ref name="donthaveem">Eliason, Michele J. [https://books.google.com/books?id=wkrcU5Z2FrcC&pg=PA55#v=onepage&q=%22straight%20pride%22%20origin Who cares?: institutional barriers to health care for lesbian, gay, and bisexual persons] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wkrcU5Z2FrcC&pg=PA55#v=onepage&q=%22straight%20pride%22%20origin |date=20220415021904 }}, p.55 (1996)</ref><ref name = "ChicagoTribune1">{{cite web |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-11-14/news/ct-oped-1114-zorn-20101114_1_gay-pride-shirts-suicide-among-gay-teens |title=When pride turns shameful |first=Eric |last=Zorn |work=[[芝加哥論壇報|Chicago Tribune]] |date=2010-11-14 |access-date=2021-02-18 |archive-date=2016-02-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201005718/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2010-11-14/news/ct-oped-1114-zorn-20101114_1_gay-pride-shirts-suicide-among-gay-teens |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

